---

This project incorporates the following third-party libraries and components:

### Core Dependencies (from python/requirements.txt)

- Name: OpenCV
  Version: >= 4.8.0
  License: BSD-3-Clause
  Homepage: https://opencv.org/
  Copyright: OpenCV team
  Notes: Used for image capture, processing, and drawing detections/tracking annotations

- Name: PySerial
  Version: >= 3.5
  License: BSD
  Homepage: https://github.com/pyserial/pyserial
  Copyright: Chris Liechti
  Notes: Used for Arduino/UART serial communication and protocol handling

- Name: NumPy
  Version: >= 1.24.0
  License: BSD
  Homepage: https://numpy.org/
  Copyright: NumPy developers
  Notes: Used for numerical computations and array operations

- Name: Ultralytics YOLOv8
  Version: >= 8.0.0
  License: AGPL-3.0
  Homepage: https://github.com/ultralytics/ultralytics
  Copyright: Ultralytics Inc.
  Notes: AI model for mosquito detection and tracking (CPU inference)

- Name: ONNX Runtime
  Version: >= 1.15.0
  License: MIT
  Homepage: https://onnxruntime.ai/
  Copyright: Microsoft Corporation
  Notes: Used for ONNX model inference with optimization for Orange Pi 5

- Name: Flask
  Version: >= 2.3.0
  License: BSD-3-Clause
  Homepage: https://flask.palletsprojects.com/
  Copyright: Armin Ronacher and contributors
  Notes: Used for HTTP-MJPEG video streaming and web interface

### Optional Dependencies

- Name: PyTorch
  Version: >= 2.0.0 (Optional - CPU version)
  License: BSD
  Homepage: https://pytorch.org/
  Notes: Optional for local YOLOv8 model inference on Orange Pi 5

- Name: RKNN Toolkit2
  Version: Latest
  License: Proprietary
  Homepage: https://github.com/rockchip-linux/rknn-toolkit2
  Notes: Optional for NPU acceleration on Orange Pi 5 RK3588 processor

### Hardware Reference Code & Examples

- Name: ZL-KPZ Control Board Example Code
  Location: docs/pt2d_sample/
  Source: 杭州众灵科技 (Hangzhou Zhongling Technology Co., Ltd.)
  Homepage: https://www.ZL-robot.com/
  Copyright: 杭州众灵科技
  License: Reference implementation (provided as-is for hardware control)
  Notes: The docs/pt2d_sample/ directory contains example code and documentation from Hangzhou Zhongling Technology 
         for controlling the ZL-KPZ bus servo control board. These examples include:
         - basic/: Simple examples demonstrating servo control methods
         - uart/: UART communication examples for bus servo commands
         - Control board documentation and command reference manuals
         All code in this directory is provided as reference material for educational and development purposes.
